glosses: to encounter, to meet by chance

examples.text: Tunceli'de tırmanış yapan dağcılar, karla kaplı arazide nesli koruma altında bulunan 10 çengel boynuzlu dağ keçisine rastladı.
examples.translation: In Tunceli, climbers ascending the snowy terrain encountered a herd of ten chamois, a protected species.

etymology: Inherited from Ottoman Turkish راستلامق (rastlamak), verb formed from راست (rast, “luck, success; encounter, meeting”), a semantic evolution of Persian راست (râst).
